issue.title: Error when resolving attributes with xml namespaces
issue.body:
I found an error in resolver which crashes on attributes with XML namespace:

```
<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" width="32" height="32" viewBox="0 0 120 120"></svg>
```

The `xmlns:link` attribute produces the following error message:

![image](https://github.com/riganti/dotvvm/assets/5599524/2ec696bb-9b80-420e-a290-a065d0c01798)

Complete error page here:

[dotvvm-error-ArgumentOutOfRangeException.zip](https://github.com/riganti/dotvvm/files/13186370/dotvvm-error-ArgumentOutOfRangeException.zip)

js translations: support Linq methods on ImmutableArray

ImmutableArray is a struct so it has custom Linq method overloads
to avoid allocations.
These are preferred by the compiler over IEnumerable<T>,
so our Linq support was broken.

Also added .AsEnumerable and few other conversion methods
to help users work around similar issues.
CompilationPage: add title to truncated table columns
CompilationPage: add Errors tab

Merge pull request #1712 from riganti/dependabot/npm_and_yarn/src/Framework/Framework/babel/traverse-7.23.2

Bump @babel/traverse from 7.17.3 to 7.23.2 in /src/Framework/Framework

Fix implicit conversion in expressions like `C ? P : null`

should fix part of #1694

CompositeControl: better handling of ambiguous GetContents, test for inheritance

According to  #1613 CompositeControl do not work with
both base and derived types defining GetContents method.
I could not replicate that, the provided example works for me,
maybe it was fixed accidentaly.

* I added test for that
* In any case, multiple GetContents overloads were handled poorly,
   I added better error for this case.

In the issue, I mentioned that it would be complex to handle
potential redefinition or "removal" of properties in the derived type.
That isn't really the case, both cases don't need any special code
* The "removal" - omission of an property in the derived type is simply ignored.
   I think that it's quite intuitive that properties can't disapear in
   derived types, if the GetContents doesn't ask for it it won't get it.
* Redefinition is already handled reasonably, since we can already
   try to redefine IncludeInPage or some capability property.

Resolves #1613

Sort the bindings in invalid command invocation error

Bindings with matching ID are most prefered,
then bindings from the correct control are prefered,
then it's sorted by the number of matching properties.

Fix whitespace padding width with tabs and Unicode combining characters

Tabs are replaced by tabs to preserve the string width,
all other characters are replaced by a single space.
Moreover we now count the unicode graphemes instead of UTF16 units.
It still has the problem that some characters (Emoji, CJK) are wider even
in monospace fonts, but that's not that easy to determine.

Suppress the uppercase html attribute warning if it must have a prefix

When setting HTML attributes on HierarchyRepeater
Item and Level capabilites, it's more readable to
uppercase the first letter, e.g. ItemClass instead of
Itemclass. However, this triggered the
"Class dotvvm property doesn't exist" warning.

Merge pull request #1718 from riganti/warning-suppress-prefixed-attribute

Suppress the uppercase html attribute warning if it must have a prefix

Merge pull request #1717 from riganti/log-warning-fix-padding

Fix whitespace padding width with tabs and Unicode combining characters

issue.title: Dynamic hide and show the EmptyItemText in ComboBox
issue.body:
I would like to dynamically use binding expression in the EmptyItemText property in ComboBox control to change whether or not item is displayed.
The property does not support null and defaults to string.Empty, but setting string.Empty behaves differently than if the attribute is not specified.


**Not specifying EmptyItemText:**
![image](https://github.com/riganti/dotvvm/assets/11502624/901884bd-d086-4d16-9ea8-c193537d023b)

**EmptyItemText="":**
![image](https://github.com/riganti/dotvvm/assets/11502624/39084aa9-6583-4573-9c51-486ec015f56a)

**EmptyItemText="{value: OsobaHodnoceniMesic.IDOsobaHodnoceniMesic == 0 ? "[Vyberte]" : null}":**
Error: Unable to get property KnockoutExpressionBindingProperty: Could not implicitly convert expression of type System.Object to System.String. Binding: {value: OsobaHodnoceniMesic.IDOsobaHodnoceniMesic == 0 ? "[Vyberte]" : null}. Property path: KnockoutExpressionBindingProperty, KnockoutJsExpressionBindingProperty.

**EmptyItemText="{value: OsobaHodnoceniMesic.IDOsobaHodnoceniMesic == 0 ? "[Vyberte]" : (string)null}":**
Error: Unable to get property KnockoutExpressionBindingProperty: Unexpected token 'OsobaHodnoceniMesic.IDOsobaHodnoceniMesic == 0 ? "[Vyberte]" : (string) ---->null<---- '. Binding: {value: OsobaHodnoceniMesic.IDOsobaHodnoceniMesic == 0 ? "[Vyberte]" : (string)null}. Property path: KnockoutExpressionBindingProperty, KnockoutJsExpressionBindingProperty, CastedExpressionBindingProperty.

**EmptyItemText="{value: OsobaHodnoceniMesic.IDOsobaHodnoceniMesic == 0 ? "[Vyberte]" : ""}":**
![image](https://github.com/riganti/dotvvm/assets/11502624/b6df7c9d-a578-4539-986f-b851f5d0493f)
For not OsobaHodnoceniMesic.IDOsobaHodnoceniMesic == 0 it is with empty EmptyItem but not without EmptyItem. I would like it to be like in first case when EmptyItemText is not specify.
